on was only 0.69 J h-1. The physiological rate with the greatest effect on growth was the absorption rate. Its relation to SFG is described by the equation SFG = 0.67 + 0.90AR (r = 0.977, R2=95.56{\%}, p{\textless}0.01). The discussion of these results is based on the growth rates that have been described for this mussel in its natural environment where habitat structure, such as the canopy provided by the eelgrass, can affect the success of the invasive mussel.},
